1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,638
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,646 --> 00:00:02,970
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:12,630 --> 00:00:16,236
(My Daughter, Ji Ni)

4
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:22,463
The phone is turned off.
You'll be connected to voicemail...

5
00:00:22,465 --> 00:00:25,063
(Episode 7)

6
00:01:01,284 --> 00:01:04,171
You said you'd take care of the funeral.
Hurry over.

7
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:06,698
What do you mean you didn't mean it?

8
00:01:06,768 --> 00:01:08,086
You're the eldest son.

9
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:10,877
Okay.

10
00:01:10,968 --> 00:01:11,968
Bye.

11
00:01:13,624 --> 00:01:14,836
Is he coming?

12
00:01:15,440 --> 00:01:16,584
Go home.

13
00:01:16,630 --> 00:01:18,238
O Reum isn't feeling well.

14
00:01:19,210 --> 00:01:21,238
I'll leave O Reum with my parents
and come back.

15
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:23,094
No, you don't have to.

16
00:01:23,096 --> 00:01:25,832
Come on. I'm the eldest daughter-in-law.

17
00:01:27,370 --> 00:01:28,627
But...

18
00:01:28,728 --> 00:01:30,177
If we don't help her...

19
00:01:30,740 --> 00:01:32,244
She can handle it herself.

20
00:01:33,856 --> 00:01:36,564
- Then I'll go, Mom.
- Okay. Go.

21
00:02:16,940 --> 00:02:19,147
(A Special Book Talk on "About Family,"
featuring author Kim In Ho)

22
00:02:37,536 --> 00:02:38,950
Why isn't the music playing?

23
00:02:40,570 --> 00:02:43,542
There's a problem with the sound,
and they're fixing it now.

24
00:02:43,570 --> 00:02:45,523
- It won't be long.
- Seriously...

25
00:02:46,985 --> 00:02:48,292
Here comes the author.

26
00:02:53,110 --> 00:02:55,614
Hello. I'm Kim In Ho.

27
00:02:55,677 --> 00:02:59,522
First, I'd like to express my thanks
to Mr. Im Joong Bin,

28
00:02:59,753 --> 00:03:03,161
the owner of Captain's Bookshop,
for hosting this wonderful event.

29
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:08,262
We're truly grateful to Mr. Im Joong Bin.

30
00:03:08,264 --> 00:03:11,586
No matter how few copies we sell,

31
00:03:11,606 --> 00:03:14,124
he gives writers like us a chance.

32
00:03:14,590 --> 00:03:16,028
Mr. Im, would you say a few words?

33
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:24,778
I've often heard people worry
that young people don't read anymore.

34
00:03:24,780 --> 00:03:26,919
But so many young people came today.

35
00:03:26,956 --> 00:03:28,632
That makes me very happy.

36
00:03:29,184 --> 00:03:31,044
It wasn't easy to arrange his visit,

37
00:03:31,065 --> 00:03:34,734
so please feel free to ask questions
and speak openly with him.

38
00:03:35,124 --> 00:03:38,139
We've also prepared some snacks.
Please help yourselves.

39
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,651
The music is finally playing.

40
00:03:54,684 --> 00:03:56,496
We'll begin the book signing now.

41
00:04:03,116 --> 00:04:05,434
Ji Hu took care of the problem.

42
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,877
Really?

43
00:04:19,168 --> 00:04:22,959
Yes, without Ji Hu,
the place would've felt so lifeless.

44
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:26,970
- You were here?
- Is it over?

45
00:04:27,748 --> 00:04:28,748
Yes.

46
00:04:29,290 --> 00:04:31,592
The sound system had to break down today,
of all days.

47
00:04:32,170 --> 00:04:34,104
But we had live music instead.

48
00:04:34,144 --> 00:04:35,766
It was much better, actually.

49
00:04:35,768 --> 00:04:37,020
It worked out well in the end.

50
00:04:37,064 --> 00:04:40,242
I heard Vice Minister Mun passed away.
We should pay our respects tonight.

51
00:04:40,244 --> 00:04:42,722
Yes, I heard the news.
I'll go home and get ready.

52
00:04:42,724 --> 00:04:44,651
I should go too. Mom called me.

53
00:04:44,660 --> 00:04:46,886
She told me to bring condolence money
and pay my respects.

54
00:04:47,350 --> 00:04:48,846
Okay, then let's go together.

55
00:04:49,330 --> 00:04:50,330
Father.

56
00:04:51,584 --> 00:04:52,886
I'll leave first.

57
00:04:52,888 --> 00:04:54,788
My son.

58
00:04:55,456 --> 00:04:58,027
- Thank you for today.
- Don't mention it.

59
00:04:58,029 --> 00:05:01,698
I told you to stop doing that.
You look like the one being hugged.

60
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:05,028
There's nothing better
than being held in my son's arms.

61
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:07,940
See you later, Mom.

62
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,668
Did you two fight?

63
00:05:17,670 --> 00:05:19,668
Why are you acting like strangers?

64
00:05:19,670 --> 00:05:22,848
He's just been busy.
What would we fight about?

65
00:05:24,508 --> 00:05:27,460
I honestly don't understand
why you're so angry.

66
00:05:29,668 --> 00:05:33,174
- You don't understand?
- No. I really don't.

67
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:35,255
It meant nothing. I was just having fun...

68
00:05:35,257 --> 00:05:36,910
That's exactly what I hate.

69
00:05:36,912 --> 00:05:38,472
Is our relationship that casual to you?

70
00:05:38,892 --> 00:05:41,106
If it meant nothing, why did you hide it?

71
00:05:41,108 --> 00:05:42,620
Because I knew you'd react like this.

72
00:05:42,660 --> 00:05:44,408
Then you shouldn't have done it.

73
00:05:44,410 --> 00:05:47,330
You had a secret account behind my back
and still planned to marry me?

74
00:05:47,650 --> 00:05:49,450
What does marriage mean to you?

75
00:05:49,488 --> 00:05:52,643
It's not that serious.
Stop making it into something bigger.

76
00:05:53,290 --> 00:05:56,216
I don't understand
why you're taking it this far.

77
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:06,840
Ji Hu, it was really nothing.

78
00:06:06,842 --> 00:06:09,526
Please forgive me just this once. Okay?

79
00:06:09,528 --> 00:06:11,362
Please.

80
00:06:13,052 --> 00:06:14,572
I'm trying to make sense of it.

81
00:06:18,619 --> 00:06:20,380
Go live in the Stone Age.

82
00:06:20,382 --> 00:06:22,500
You don't belong in the 21st century.

83
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,776
Seriously...

84
00:06:27,824 --> 00:06:29,783
I didn't say anything.

85
00:07:12,372 --> 00:07:15,186
- Seung Hyun.
- Yes.

86
00:07:15,188 --> 00:07:19,320
I want you to take care of my funeral.

87
00:07:21,370 --> 00:07:23,946
- Why should I...
- You're my first child.

88
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,698
You're my first love.

89
00:07:27,892 --> 00:07:29,810
You should focus on getting better.

90
00:07:29,924 --> 00:07:31,740
Don't think about things
that haven't happened yet.

91
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,210
I don't have much time left.

92
00:07:33,768 --> 00:07:35,828
- Please do this for me.
- That makes no sense.

93
00:07:35,830 --> 00:07:37,476
The person you lived with should do it.

94
00:07:42,724 --> 00:07:44,731
Don't leave the two women
to face it alone.

95
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:48,715
I want you by their side.
Please do this for me.

96
00:08:08,420 --> 00:08:10,419
What? When?

97
00:08:12,104 --> 00:08:15,008
Really? When did he pass away?

98
00:08:17,144 --> 00:08:20,767
Yes, Ji Ni. I'm on my way.

99
00:08:21,164 --> 00:08:23,127
Ji Ni, don't cry.

100
00:08:23,231 --> 00:08:25,386
Okay. I'll be there soon.

101
00:08:32,404 --> 00:08:34,920
Honey, no.

102
00:08:34,972 --> 00:08:36,577
Honey, not now.

103
00:08:57,752 --> 00:09:01,287
The room is set, the flowers are chosen,
and the mourning clothes are ready.

104
00:09:01,852 --> 00:09:04,664
- I need the list of family members.
- "The list of family members?"

105
00:09:05,724 --> 00:09:07,523
What should we do?

106
00:09:09,517 --> 00:09:11,044
Spouse, No Yeong Ju.

107
00:09:11,096 --> 00:09:12,797
Sons, Seung Hyun and Seung Woo.

108
00:09:12,804 --> 00:09:14,998
- Seung Hyun.
- Let's follow the documents.

109
00:09:15,550 --> 00:09:17,611
When he asked me to handle the funeral,

110
00:09:18,196 --> 00:09:19,518
this must've been what he wanted.

111
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:22,610
But shouldn't we include
his daughter's name?

112
00:09:23,072 --> 00:09:24,836
Should we add Ji Ni under Seung Woo?

113
00:09:25,990 --> 00:09:27,657
Let's just keep it simple, Mom.

114
00:09:30,657 --> 00:09:33,215
(Chief mourner, Cha Seung Hyun,
Relationship to deceased, Eldest son)

115
00:09:43,392 --> 00:09:44,703
(Room 1, Cha Min Ki, Spouse, No Yeong Ju)

116
00:09:44,705 --> 00:09:46,143
(Sons, Cha Seung Hyun, Cha Seung Woo)

117
00:09:48,912 --> 00:09:50,544
My goodness.

118
00:09:50,936 --> 00:09:52,298
My goodness...

119
00:09:55,602 --> 00:09:58,222
- Ji Ni!
- Mom!

120
00:09:58,729 --> 00:10:00,173
How did your dad pass away?

121
00:10:00,476 --> 00:10:01,916
You were with him when he passed, right?

122
00:10:03,310 --> 00:10:07,486
When I got there,
Dad was about to pass away.

123
00:10:07,533 --> 00:10:09,301
I was with him when he passed.

124
00:10:11,108 --> 00:10:12,142
Yeong Ju.

125
00:10:12,176 --> 00:10:14,534
Yeong Ju, what are you doing?

126
00:10:14,583 --> 00:10:18,346
Why are you wearing mourning clothes
while Ji Ni is standing out here?

127
00:10:18,383 --> 00:10:20,306
And what's with that sign outside?

128
00:10:20,770 --> 00:10:23,894
Yeong Ju, is this why
you've been visiting the hospital?

129
00:10:23,918 --> 00:10:26,038
- Watch what you say!
- "Watch what I say?"

130
00:10:26,143 --> 00:10:28,511
He's my husband and my daughter's dad!

131
00:10:29,290 --> 00:10:32,290
Yeong Ju, do you even have his picture?

132
00:10:32,503 --> 00:10:35,556
Are you going to enlarge that picture
from 25 years ago?

133
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:40,383
Do you really want to keep doing this
until the very end?

134
00:10:40,408 --> 00:10:42,827
Dad asked me to handle his funeral.

135
00:10:42,829 --> 00:10:45,360
- Because I'm his eldest son!
- "Eldest son?"

136
00:10:45,661 --> 00:10:47,618
So you're lording that over us?

137
00:10:47,643 --> 00:10:50,512
I know this hurts,
but this is the right thing.

138
00:10:50,775 --> 00:10:53,465
- The documents...
- Those damn documents!

139
00:10:53,529 --> 00:10:57,742
You stole someone else's husband,
yet you have a lot to say.

140
00:10:57,769 --> 00:11:02,591
I had to give you a piece of my mind
before I die.

141
00:11:02,862 --> 00:11:05,319
You broke my sister's heart...

142
00:11:05,343 --> 00:11:08,834
and made Yeong Ju shut herself off
her whole life.

143
00:11:08,906 --> 00:11:10,540
You walked right into this.

144
00:11:10,562 --> 00:11:13,244
You have no conscience. You bitch!

145
00:11:13,246 --> 00:11:14,882
Stop it!

146
00:11:15,279 --> 00:11:17,404
- Aunt!
- Let go of me!

147
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:21,924
- Mom!
- Taking her side because she's your mom?

148
00:11:21,948 --> 00:11:24,416
You're two of a kind.

149
00:11:27,378 --> 00:11:30,358
- Who do you think you're spitting at?
- Go ahead, you bitch!

150
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:32,015
What are you going to do, glare at me?

151
00:11:32,950 --> 00:11:35,061
Yeah, those precious documents of yours.

152
00:11:35,086 --> 00:11:38,891
It's not some fancy diploma.
Go ahead, brag about it all you want.

153
00:11:38,916 --> 00:11:40,651
Who do you think you're scaring?

154
00:11:41,170 --> 00:11:42,670
Ji Ni, let's go.

155
00:11:47,546 --> 00:11:49,677
Excuse me? Another one?

156
00:11:49,679 --> 00:11:52,154
Yes, please open another funeral room.

157
00:11:52,156 --> 00:11:53,397
Put my name as the chief mourner.

158
00:11:53,422 --> 00:11:55,178
- Mom.
- Stay out of this.

159
00:11:55,586 --> 00:11:59,193
Go home and bring the pictures
of your dad that you prepared.

160
00:11:59,239 --> 00:12:01,145
Bring some family photos too.

161
00:12:01,272 --> 00:12:02,486
And your drawings.

162
00:12:02,963 --> 00:12:06,588
I want to decorate the entrance nicely
for the mourners. Is that okay?

163
00:12:09,789 --> 00:12:12,151
(Room 1, Cha Min Ki, Spouse, No Yeong Ju,
Sons, Cha Seung Hyun, Cha Seung Woo)

164
00:12:12,167 --> 00:12:14,069
(VIP Room 1, Cha Min Ki,
Spouse, Na Se Ri, Daughter, Na Ji Ni)

165
00:12:45,273 --> 00:12:46,529
(Haemyeong University Hospital,
Funeral Hall)

166
00:12:46,554 --> 00:12:49,322
That one goes over here,
against this wall.

167
00:12:55,109 --> 00:12:56,529
The wreath too.

168
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:58,584
- Put it against this wall.
- Yes.

169
00:12:58,609 --> 00:13:00,655
Whose name is on the wreath?

170
00:13:00,679 --> 00:13:01,735
One moment.

171
00:13:02,259 --> 00:13:03,545
Director Cha Seung Woo?

172
00:13:03,676 --> 00:13:05,452
- Then put it here.
- Yes.

173
00:13:13,876 --> 00:13:16,148
Excuse me. That wreath goes over here.

174
00:13:16,335 --> 00:13:19,067
Against this wall. Move it closer.

175
00:13:19,477 --> 00:13:20,710
Sir!

176
00:13:22,655 --> 00:13:26,051
Thank you for coming. Please come inside.

177
00:13:28,554 --> 00:13:32,369
Thank you so much. Go on in.

178
00:13:41,211 --> 00:13:43,526
Dad, when are you coming to Seoul?

179
00:13:43,963 --> 00:13:46,801
You should come
to my father-in-law's funeral.

180
00:13:46,803 --> 00:13:48,357
You don't have to.

181
00:13:48,358 --> 00:13:51,034
No, it's okay if you don't come.
Just send wreaths.

182
00:13:51,058 --> 00:13:52,306
Send ten.

183
00:13:52,330 --> 00:13:55,133
And tell your employees
to come pay their respects.

184
00:13:55,135 --> 00:13:57,748
- Dad, you can pay them for their time.
- Mai!

185
00:13:59,574 --> 00:14:02,335
Anyway, Dad,
make sure you send the wreaths.

186
00:14:02,643 --> 00:14:04,610
I'll explain later.

187
00:14:05,836 --> 00:14:07,540
Why are you stopping me?

188
00:14:07,723 --> 00:14:09,397
I'm feeling really spiteful right now.

189
00:14:11,650 --> 00:14:12,689
Come out.

190
00:14:17,420 --> 00:14:18,633
You want to combine them?

191
00:14:18,635 --> 00:14:20,242
What are you doing?

192
00:14:20,266 --> 00:14:21,939
You're embarrassing yourselves.

193
00:14:21,970 --> 00:14:24,849
I didn't ask you to be the chief mourner
so we could compete.

194
00:14:24,910 --> 00:14:27,562
Before he left,
he sincerely apologized to you all,

195
00:14:28,219 --> 00:14:31,076
and I wanted to honor his final wish
by handling his funeral,

196
00:14:32,826 --> 00:14:33,919
but this...

197
00:14:34,376 --> 00:14:36,280
doesn't feel like something
either of us should be doing.

198
00:14:36,443 --> 00:14:37,768
I don't know.

199
00:14:37,899 --> 00:14:39,896
No. We have our pride.

200
00:14:39,921 --> 00:14:41,476
I can't let you lose again.

201
00:14:41,501 --> 00:14:43,024
This isn't about winning or losing.

202
00:14:43,049 --> 00:14:44,791
That woman isn't very smart.

203
00:14:44,816 --> 00:14:47,383
If she keeps this up,
she's only embarrassing herself.

204
00:14:48,791 --> 00:14:50,308
Let's just leave it.

205
00:14:50,342 --> 00:14:53,612
Let her go all the way
and see who ends up looking foolish.

206
00:14:53,830 --> 00:14:56,889
If she's the other woman,
she should keep quiet and stand beside us.

207
00:14:56,914 --> 00:14:58,827
Is this really something
to be so proud of?

208
00:15:01,014 --> 00:15:03,918
You know how I lived with him.

209
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:05,359
Of course.

210
00:15:05,656 --> 00:15:07,898
I used to envy you so much, Se Ri.

211
00:15:07,929 --> 00:15:10,119
I thought you had a perfect family.

212
00:15:10,336 --> 00:15:11,664
"Perfect?" Not at all.

213
00:15:11,689 --> 00:15:14,008
I was hurting inside the whole time.

214
00:15:14,010 --> 00:15:15,244
You did well.

215
00:15:15,269 --> 00:15:17,023
If you've lived well and held it together,
that's a win.

216
00:15:17,025 --> 00:15:18,545
What's the point of that?

217
00:15:18,570 --> 00:15:22,362
No wonder Director Cha suffered so much
and passed away early.

218
00:15:22,386 --> 00:15:24,565
It's such a shame.

219
00:15:25,375 --> 00:15:27,375
- Mom.
- Yes?

220
00:15:27,679 --> 00:15:30,497
Excuse me for a moment.

221
00:15:37,189 --> 00:15:39,447
You really can't judge people
by appearances.

222
00:15:44,162 --> 00:15:46,589
Do you have to do everything
just because he asked?

223
00:15:46,776 --> 00:15:49,246
First because he was sick,
and now because he's dead.

224
00:15:49,456 --> 00:15:51,495
At least you should get a grip!

225
00:15:51,535 --> 00:15:53,086
Are you going to tell people at work?

226
00:15:53,289 --> 00:15:55,085
That we had a father all along?

227
00:15:55,136 --> 00:15:57,029
That for 25 years, he had an affair...

228
00:15:57,053 --> 00:16:00,009
and that mom and all of us
lived in hiding like ghosts?

229
00:16:00,034 --> 00:16:02,801
Mom stayed by him until the very end.

230
00:16:02,825 --> 00:16:03,886
That's enough.

231
00:16:03,910 --> 00:16:06,126
Unless you're planning to spread the word
about this messed-up family funeral,

232
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:07,519
stop right there!

233
00:16:07,694 --> 00:16:10,204
Seung Woo, no, Brother-in-law.

234
00:16:10,263 --> 00:16:14,100
Think long-term. Don't be so naive.

235
00:16:14,179 --> 00:16:15,477
Stay out of this.

236
00:16:15,502 --> 00:16:18,477
Handling the funeral means
acknowledging you're his son,

237
00:16:18,479 --> 00:16:21,242
and that'll help you later
with the inheritance.

238
00:16:22,778 --> 00:16:25,787
I was going to tell you this later, but...

239
00:16:26,296 --> 00:16:28,360
your father's company and house,

240
00:16:28,569 --> 00:16:30,307
who do you think they'll end up going to?

241
00:16:31,063 --> 00:16:33,585
Hello?

242
00:16:36,176 --> 00:16:37,637
This is frustrating.

243
00:16:39,936 --> 00:16:41,496
Were you always this calculating?

244
00:16:41,563 --> 00:16:43,350
I feel like I got tricked
into marrying you.

245
00:16:43,656 --> 00:16:45,563
You're only realizing that now?

246
00:16:45,916 --> 00:16:50,798
Didn't you know I set everything up
and waited for you to fall right in?

247
00:16:50,876 --> 00:16:53,659
Too late now.
Our firstborn is already running around.

248
00:16:55,102 --> 00:16:58,120
I'll take O Reum home
and come back tomorrow morning.

249
00:16:58,144 --> 00:16:59,507
Want me to drive you?

250
00:16:59,710 --> 00:17:03,427
I'll take mother with me,
so you stay here and hold things down.

251
00:17:03,838 --> 00:17:04,951
Okay.

252
00:17:13,245 --> 00:17:14,245
(VIP Room 1)

253
00:17:14,256 --> 00:17:16,558
Let's go home and get some rest.

254
00:17:16,583 --> 00:17:18,438
We'll have a lot of guests tomorrow.

255
00:17:18,462 --> 00:17:19,786
I don't want to.

256
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:21,150
We won't sleep next to dad anymore.

257
00:17:21,151 --> 00:17:23,688
Enough about dad already.

258
00:17:31,412 --> 00:17:33,205
You really picked the wrong person
to mess with.

259
00:17:33,787 --> 00:17:36,257
Vietnamese chili peppers are spicier
than Korean ones.

260
00:17:36,748 --> 00:17:39,332
Yeong Ju, what is she even saying?

261
00:17:39,379 --> 00:17:41,886
You don't usually care what others say.

262
00:17:44,436 --> 00:17:46,158
What's her problem now?

263
00:17:48,686 --> 00:17:50,066
Do you really have to go this far?

264
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:51,205
This is humiliating.

265
00:17:51,243 --> 00:17:54,472
You're one to talk.
Do you have to be like this?

266
00:17:54,782 --> 00:17:57,080
Are you that obsessed with paperwork?

267
00:17:57,202 --> 00:17:58,946
You showed up when he was sick.

268
00:17:58,990 --> 00:18:01,320
Fine, I let that slide.

269
00:18:01,343 --> 00:18:05,387
He had kids and wanted to apologize.
I let it slide 100 times over.

270
00:18:05,389 --> 00:18:07,268
But this? No way.

271
00:18:07,293 --> 00:18:09,593
What gives you the right to be
the chief mourner?

272
00:18:09,617 --> 00:18:11,026
The eldest son?

273
00:18:11,061 --> 00:18:13,499
That doesn't mean anything these days.

274
00:18:18,301 --> 00:18:20,585
Whether it means something or not,

275
00:18:20,598 --> 00:18:22,341
let's see how this ends.

276
00:18:22,377 --> 00:18:23,770
Who are you to butt in?

277
00:18:23,794 --> 00:18:25,723
Me? The eldest daughter-in-law.

278
00:18:25,747 --> 00:18:27,537
The eldest daughter-in-law...

279
00:18:29,099 --> 00:18:31,056
You really picked the wrong person
to mess with.

280
00:18:31,163 --> 00:18:34,307
I'm tougher and more tenacious than you.

281
00:18:35,911 --> 00:18:37,834
Unbelievable.

282
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:43,517
Mom, can't we combine the two funerals?

283
00:18:43,541 --> 00:18:44,541
What?

284
00:18:44,569 --> 00:18:45,962
What's wrong with you now?

285
00:18:45,964 --> 00:18:48,490
I just want dad to rest in peace.

286
00:18:48,515 --> 00:18:51,428
- I don't care who hosts the funeral.
- Don't say another word.

287
00:18:52,473 --> 00:18:53,485
I'm leaving.

288
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:55,274
Call me if anything happens.

289
00:19:07,209 --> 00:19:08,294
Dad.

290
00:19:09,089 --> 00:19:12,054
We ended up having two funerals.

291
00:19:12,973 --> 00:19:14,516
That must hurt, right?

292
00:19:15,923 --> 00:19:18,544
I don't know what to do either, Dad.

293
00:19:51,145 --> 00:19:53,673
- When did you arrive?
- I got mad making ramen, so I came.

294
00:19:55,727 --> 00:19:59,221
- Where are Mom and your wife?
- They went home. You must've missed them.

295
00:19:59,223 --> 00:20:00,752
But why do you look so down?

296
00:20:01,592 --> 00:20:03,348
Don't tell me you're mourning him.

297
00:20:03,524 --> 00:20:04,750
No way.

298
00:20:05,673 --> 00:20:07,630
Still, it feels kind of strange.

299
00:20:09,226 --> 00:20:12,564
I only remember him walking out on us,

300
00:20:13,394 --> 00:20:16,483
so who was he to his other family
that they're grieving him like this?

301
00:20:18,749 --> 00:20:21,490
- This makes me feel sick.
- Then clear it away.

302
00:20:22,048 --> 00:20:23,917
If Grandpa were here,
he'd come at us with his cane.

303
00:20:25,629 --> 00:20:28,023
It's been ages since he swung that cane.

304
00:20:29,043 --> 00:20:33,310
This makes us look like we're still
hung up on that man.

305
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:36,865
- That's what annoys me.
- I was thinking about that too,

306
00:20:37,622 --> 00:20:39,985
but now I refuse to back down.

307
00:20:39,987 --> 00:20:42,558
As Mai said, they could've just
joined us quietly,

308
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:45,229
but they went and set up
their own funeral hall. That makes me mad.

309
00:20:45,231 --> 00:20:48,686
- They're ignoring us to the very end.
- "We lived with him." That's their point.

310
00:20:51,670 --> 00:20:55,945
Now I finally understand
why Mom refused to give in.

311
00:20:57,681 --> 00:21:00,054
This urge to make sure everyone knows...

312
00:21:00,528 --> 00:21:04,886
that it all began as an affair...
Why am I so petty?

313
00:21:09,594 --> 00:21:11,895
Why are you acting like this too?

314
00:21:13,738 --> 00:21:17,628
I'll smash this whole damn place up.

315
00:21:19,153 --> 00:21:21,432
Seung Woo, don't make things worse.

316
00:21:21,434 --> 00:21:22,822
Hey!

317
00:21:23,918 --> 00:21:26,108
Stop making a pathetic scene
and clear this out.

318
00:21:27,130 --> 00:21:28,641
What's wrong with you?

319
00:21:29,665 --> 00:21:32,240
You're Na Ji Ni, not Cha Ji Ni.

320
00:21:32,242 --> 00:21:35,905
So why are you making a fuss
about arranging this man's funeral?

321
00:21:36,288 --> 00:21:38,827
Have you lost all sense,
just like your mother?

322
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:40,273
You and your mother...

323
00:21:40,315 --> 00:21:43,337
have nothing to do with that man.

324
00:21:43,407 --> 00:21:46,706
The man you keep calling "that man"
is my dad.

325
00:21:46,708 --> 00:21:48,361
No matter what anyone says, he's my dad.

326
00:21:48,362 --> 00:21:51,214
He gave me life, raised me, and loved me.

327
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:54,686
Then,

328
00:21:55,508 --> 00:21:57,507
keep those feelings hidden
until the very end.

329
00:21:57,508 --> 00:21:59,877
Don't ruin someone else's funeral!

330
00:21:59,879 --> 00:22:04,312
Tell your mother to clear this out
first thing tomorrow,

331
00:22:04,733 --> 00:22:06,506
or I'll make a scene and finally let out
all the anger I've been holding back.

332
00:22:06,507 --> 00:22:07,968
Please, that's enough.

333
00:22:07,969 --> 00:22:09,024
Look at you!

334
00:22:09,026 --> 00:22:12,077
He's our dad. Why don't I have the right?

335
00:22:12,079 --> 00:22:13,597
Do you really think...

336
00:22:14,076 --> 00:22:15,957
you and I are on the same level?

337
00:22:16,535 --> 00:22:19,987
- Get out. You're disgusting.
- I don't like this situation either.

338
00:22:20,322 --> 00:22:22,521
But this is between our parents,

339
00:22:22,904 --> 00:22:24,027
and I'm just...

340
00:22:25,214 --> 00:22:28,551
his daughter, so as his child,

341
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:31,231
I want to mourn my dad.

342
00:22:32,687 --> 00:22:35,392
This makes it easier for both sides
to receive guests.

343
00:22:35,434 --> 00:22:38,262
- It may be embarrassing, but...
- Do it yourself.

344
00:22:38,813 --> 00:22:40,417
I won't do it.

345
00:22:41,753 --> 00:22:44,102
We're both his children,
grieving our father.

346
00:22:44,469 --> 00:22:47,097
I hope we can at least speak respectfully.

347
00:22:47,098 --> 00:22:49,105
Who says you're family?

348
00:22:49,692 --> 00:22:52,128
You've got some nerve.

349
00:22:54,102 --> 00:23:00,542
Get rid of those leeches
who've ruined our lives.

350
00:23:01,003 --> 00:23:02,734
Get them out!

351
00:23:03,806 --> 00:23:08,048
- Aren't you going to remove them? Now!
- Seung Woo, don't do this!

352
00:23:08,588 --> 00:23:11,852
Seung Hyun,
listen to what this girl is saying.

353
00:23:11,854 --> 00:23:14,193
We let it slide,
and she really thinks she's one of us.

354
00:23:14,194 --> 00:23:15,923
What makes you different?

355
00:23:18,146 --> 00:23:22,349
I didn't choose to be born either,
so just stop.

356
00:23:24,026 --> 00:23:26,585
There's no point. Let's go.

357
00:23:34,077 --> 00:23:37,467
That's why I told you
we shouldn't do this.

358
00:23:52,911 --> 00:23:54,806
But I think you said
something wrong earlier.

359
00:23:57,237 --> 00:23:58,699
- What?
- None of us wanted this,

360
00:23:58,700 --> 00:24:00,192
and it all happened unintentionally,

361
00:24:00,775 --> 00:24:04,592
and other people may not
think you're guilty,

362
00:24:05,055 --> 00:24:07,102
but you shouldn't have said that to us.

363
00:24:08,170 --> 00:24:10,791
Have you ever suddenly found yourself
in a single-parent family?

364
00:24:11,643 --> 00:24:13,750
Have you ever had a dad
who was there one day and gone the next?

365
00:24:14,466 --> 00:24:15,932
- Look...
- When you say things so shamelessly,

366
00:24:15,933 --> 00:24:17,514
I don't think I can let that slide,

367
00:24:17,516 --> 00:24:19,084
so I'll make this clear.

368
00:24:19,810 --> 00:24:22,388
Just because I stay quiet
doesn't mean I understand you.

369
00:24:22,390 --> 00:24:25,937
The dad my brother misses,
the husband my mom lost!

370
00:24:26,694 --> 00:24:28,777
You and your mom took him away.

371
00:24:29,968 --> 00:24:31,559
Don't casually claim you're innocent.

372
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:33,038
Not in front of me.

373
00:24:33,819 --> 00:24:35,225
Never say it again.

374
00:24:38,263 --> 00:24:39,855
All of you...

375
00:24:40,687 --> 00:24:43,465
comfort your mom
and even grab me by the collar,

376
00:24:44,998 --> 00:24:47,241
but I can't comfort mine.

377
00:24:48,181 --> 00:24:50,643
And I can't blame her either.

378
00:24:52,695 --> 00:24:55,321
I'm sad, but there's no one to tell.

379
00:24:57,013 --> 00:24:58,838
Do I have to listen
to all that whining too?

380
00:25:02,163 --> 00:25:03,868
I guess I'm the only one who feels it,

381
00:25:04,647 --> 00:25:06,539
this strange sense of similarity.

382
00:25:06,541 --> 00:25:09,484
- What?
- A single-parent family overnight?

383
00:25:11,423 --> 00:25:14,680
From the moment I was born,
I was a criminal's daughter.

384
00:25:21,165 --> 00:25:22,847
I'm sorry.

385
00:25:23,182 --> 00:25:25,572
I don't know what I did wrong,

386
00:25:26,270 --> 00:25:27,669
but I'm sorry.

387
00:25:32,324 --> 00:25:33,746
Right.

388
00:25:35,266 --> 00:25:37,738
Sometimes you have to take responsibility
even when you didn't cause it.

389
00:25:39,195 --> 00:25:40,795
You'll understand with time.

390
00:26:21,206 --> 00:26:22,807
Dad, I hate you the most.

391
00:26:23,938 --> 00:26:25,602
I really hate you.

392
00:26:29,297 --> 00:26:32,198
You made me bow my head and apologize...

393
00:26:33,110 --> 00:26:34,812
and then just left?

394
00:26:37,522 --> 00:26:39,614
Did you think I liked you?

395
00:26:43,232 --> 00:26:44,406
No.

396
00:26:45,892 --> 00:26:50,987
I'm probably the one
who hates you the most.

397
00:26:51,812 --> 00:26:53,729
Is love enough?

398
00:26:53,955 --> 00:26:55,996
Are your feelings the only ones
that are real?

399
00:27:02,143 --> 00:27:03,336
Then,

400
00:27:04,866 --> 00:27:07,036
what about me?

401
00:27:09,751 --> 00:27:11,914
I really hate you.

402
00:27:13,307 --> 00:27:15,031
It's over now.

403
00:28:15,639 --> 00:28:18,931
(Family Register)

404
00:28:19,022 --> 00:28:21,034
Now I see why your dad dropped dead.

405
00:28:21,042 --> 00:28:23,976
I endured it for 20 years. Let's stop here
and walk away. I'm sick of it.

406
00:28:23,978 --> 00:28:26,405
Why are you even here?
How dare you show your face?

407
00:28:26,406 --> 00:28:28,917
Looks like you still haven't been promoted
to legal wife.

408
00:28:28,919 --> 00:28:31,547
Hang in there. Once tomorrow's over,
it's really done.

409
00:28:31,549 --> 00:28:34,247
It was really hard for me to love you.

410
00:28:34,248 --> 00:28:37,213
Uncle, is she someone
you're seeing or something?

411
00:28:39,212 --> 00:28:41,212
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
